+    You can pass ``with_counts=True`` to also include the number of
+    items in each group, yielding ``(grouper, list, count)`` tuples
+    instead. This avoids having to use ``|list|length`` on the items to
+    get the size of a group.
+
+    .. sourcecode:: jinja
+
+        <ul>{% for city, items, count in users|groupby("city", with_counts=True) %}
+          <li>{{ city }} ({{ count }})</li>
+        {% endfor %}</ul>
+
+    .. versionchanged:: 3.1
+        Added the ``with_counts`` parameter.
+
     .. versionchanged:: 3.0
         Added the ``default`` parameter.
 
